# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# web/ environment template — copy to `.env.local` and fill in.
#
#   cp web/.env.example web/.env.local
#
# `.env.local` is git-ignored (see web/.gitignore → `.env*.local`); this file
# is the committed reference so contributors know which variables exist.
#
# NOTE: variables prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_ are inlined into the client bundle
# at build time. They are therefore PUBLIC (visible to anyone using the app) and
# must never hold secrets.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Absolute base URL of the Django API, baked into the build.
#
# Usually LEAVE UNSET: the app falls back to the relative path `/fininzen/api`
# (same origin), which is what production uses. Only set this if you need to
# point the build at a different API host.
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE=
